<subSubSection id="30CE57B00670C67C0E814B06119392E1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FD3A2D056E29D70C91176C90A0F835F6" lastPageNumber="38" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="151275024B131B5C0355469A37D8380E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">Bodianus aya Bloch, 1790</taxonomicName>
, described from Brazil after a pre-Linnaean work by the Dutch naturalist Marcgrave (1648), has been considered a 
<taxonomicName id="BBA0217D2826FC591BE53C95D79D2355" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6DB2A54F-6D0D-4121-8610-1234D8995F5F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lutjanus Bloch 1790:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lutjanus</taxonomicName>
species (e.g. Jordan &amp; Fesler 1893, Meek &amp; Hildebrand 1925, Lima 1965, Anderson 1967). However, because types are not extant and the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="3A8BAEBCC7EC233A450045F2157F0018" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">B. aya</taxonomicName>
is not informative, the assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="707D0597F80B8F85FE3269E498CCB51D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">B. aya</taxonomicName>
within the family Lutjanidae has been controversial. Lima (1965) and Anderson (1967) recognized 
<taxonomicName id="8F395C20977F80F26805F83DEE596244" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">Lutjanus aya (Bloch)</taxonomicName>
as the commercially important “red snapper.” On the other hand, Rivas (1966) regarded 
<taxonomicName id="CE28E1ECE48ED2175EACEC56662FF287" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">Bodianus aya Bloch</taxonomicName>
as a sciaenid, and distinguished two species of red snappers, the northern red snapper, 
<taxonomicName id="165744EC6768A0EFC896271AF0696244" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="campechanus">L. campechanus (Poey)</taxonomicName>
, and the southern red snapper, 
<taxonomicName id="ECE95BD10E836233FE026D142E4676E6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="purpureus">L. purpureus Poey</taxonomicName>
, as previously suggested by Hildebrand &amp; Ginsburg (1926) and Ginsburg (1930). Allen (1985), apparently following Rivas (1966), did not include 
<taxonomicName id="2101831751A5BC866E7A559D2C70E4D4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">L. aya</taxonomicName>
in his list of nominal species of Lutjanidae. We examined Marcgrave ’s (1648) and Bloch’s (1790) descriptions and plates and could not assign 
<taxonomicName id="021E799070A6C874E94D98157B7420C3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">B. aya</taxonomicName>
to any known Atlantic 
<taxonomicName id="23E4C98D22E2924D2DF6643D9B755950" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6DB2A54F-6D0D-4121-8610-1234D8995F5F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lutjanus Bloch 1790:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lutjanus</taxonomicName>
species, and consider it to be an unidentifiable nominal species, as already suggested by Eschmeyer (1998). For the purpose of nomenclatural stability a petition should be submitted to the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature requesting the suppression of the name 
<taxonomicName id="F4670BA04C63FAC7A97BB294F00955F6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA8B4E61-5C3A-493A-8107-DE629122FA6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bodianus aya Bloch 1790:45" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aya">Bodianus aya Bloch, 1790</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
